---
import TokenizationDemo from '../components/viz/TokenizationDemo';
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Visual foundation demo"
  description="Proof of Agent Atlas's scene-driven visualization architecture."
>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6 px-6 py-16">
    <header>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Visual foundation demo</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">
        A minimal walkthrough — raw text → token boundaries → token ids → context window —
        proving the scene-driven visual architecture (pure scene functions, Stepper,
        TokenStream, ContextWindowBar). The full Tokens lesson builds on this.
      </p>
    </header>

    {/* client:visible — hydrate only when scrolled into view. The step-0 scene is
        server-rendered, so the page teaches before (and without) JavaScript. */}
    <TokenizationDemo client:visible />

    <noscript>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">
        JavaScript is disabled: you are seeing the first step. The step controls need JavaScript;
        the content above is complete for step 1 of 5.
      </p>
    </noscript>
  </main>
</Base>
